Philippine Stock Movers: Information Capital Technology, Philex

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p   a n d   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-09-05T04:16:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/philippine-stock-movers-information-capital-technology-philex.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippines trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.2 percent to
4,382.56.  Information Capital Technology Ventures Inc. (ICTV)  , a
Philippine media and information technology company, surged 50
percent to 66 centavos, its biggest percentage gain since
September 2007. The company signed a memorandum of understanding
with Huawei International Pte. Ltd. and Next Mobile Inc. to
explore a possible “business relationship,” it said in a
disclosure to the stock exchange today.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the largest Philippine metals
producer, gained 2 percent to 27.55 pesos, the first advance in
three days. The company produced 1.48 billion pesos ($35
million) of minerals in August and shipped 1 billion pesos of
resources, a stock-exchange filing said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at 
